concept("grid",|std:///experiments/RascalTutor/Courses/Rascal/Libraries/Vis/Figure/Figures/grid/grid.concept|,["\<warning\>Static Error: prompt:///:1,58: The called signature: grid(list[Figure], FProperty, FProperty),\</warning\>","\<warning\>Static Error: prompt:///:1,58: The called signature: grid(list[Figure], FProperty, FProperty),\</warning\>","\<warning\>Static Error: prompt:///:1,58: The called signature: grid(list[Figure], FProperty, FProperty),\</warning\>"],[],{"hgap","width","vgap"},"","",""," \<code\>grid(list[list[Figure]] figs, FProperty props...)\</code\>\n",{}," Layout figures in a grid. Place figures on a fixed grid. The \<a href=\"/show?concept=width\"\>width\</a\> property determines the horizontal size of the grid\n while the vertical size is determined automatically.\n The \<a href=\"/show?concept=hgap\"\>hgap\</a\> and \<a href=\"/show?concept=vgap\"\>vgap\</a\> properties determine the distance between grid points.\n"," \<warning\>Static Error: prompt:///:1,58: The called signature: grid(list[Figure], FProperty, FProperty),\</warning\>\<pre class=\"listing\"\>b1 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Red\"));\nb2 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Blue\"));\nb3 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Yellow\"));\nb4 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Green\"));\nb5 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Purple\"));\nb6 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Orange\"));\nb7 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Silver\"));\nrender(grid([b1, b2, b3, b4, b5, b6, b7], width(200), gap(100)));\n\</pre\> gives:\n \<br/\>\n\<br/\>\n\n \<br/\>\n\<br/\>\n\n \<img class=\"TutorImg\"  title=\"grid1\" alt=\"grid1\" src=\"Courses/Rascal/Libraries/Vis/Figure/Figures/grid/g1.png\"\>\n \<br/\>\n\<br/\>\n\n Varying the sizes of \<code\>b2\</code\> and \<code\>b5\</code\>:\n \<warning\>Static Error: prompt:///:1,58: The called signature: grid(list[Figure], FProperty, FProperty),\</warning\>\<pre class=\"listing\"\>b1 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Red\"));\nb2 = box(size(60,30), fillColor(\"Blue\"));\nb3 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Yellow\"));\nb4 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Green\"));\nb5 = box(size(80,80), fillColor(\"Purple\"));\nb6 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Orange\"));\nb7 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Silver\"));\nrender(grid([b1, b2, b3, b4, b5, b6, b7], width(200), gap(100)));\n\</pre\> gives:\n \<br/\>\n\<br/\>\n\n \<br/\>\n\<br/\>\n\n \<img class=\"TutorImg\"  title=\"grid2\" alt=\"grid2\" src=\"Courses/Rascal/Libraries/Vis/Figure/Figures/grid/g2.png\"\>\n \<br/\>\n\<br/\>\n\n Varying the alignment of \<code\>b2\</code\> and \<code\>b5\</code\> gives:\n \<warning\>Static Error: prompt:///:1,58: The called signature: grid(list[Figure], FProperty, FProperty),\</warning\>\<pre class=\"listing\"\>b1 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Red\"));\nb2 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Blue\"), left(), top());\nb3 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Yellow\"));\nb4 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Green\"));\nb5 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Purple\"), bottom(), right());\nb6 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Orange\"));\nb7 = box(size(50,50), fillColor(\"Silver\"));\nrender(grid([b1, b2, b3, b4, b5, b6, b7], width(200), gap(100)));\n\</pre\> gives:\n \<br/\>\n\<br/\>\n\n \<img class=\"TutorImg\"  title=\"grid3\" alt=\"grid3\" src=\"Courses/Rascal/Libraries/Vis/Figure/Figures/grid/g3.png\"\>\n",""," The distance between grid points does not include the size of the figures that are placed\n on the grid points. If overlaps of figures are not desired, then the horizontal (or vertical) gap size \n should be larger than the largest width (height) of the figures to be placed on the grid.\n",[])